 Alice - Alice Detectives are appealing to public members to assist with information or whereabouts of a 37-year-old man of foreign descent. "According to his passport in the possession of police,  his name is Ali Abbasi and is a Malawian citizen," said police spokesperson, Captain Khaya Tonjeni. "He is believed to be a key person that can assist in finalizing a case currently under investigation by Alice SAPS." Capt Tonjeni said that anyone with information about his whereabouts is kindly requested to share the information with the Investigation Officers, Sgt Siphelo Poyo-082 301 8351 or Office landline no-040 657 4903  Or Or Sgt Daluxolo Xhela- 0825654272 "All correspondence and information will be treated confidential." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 